Not covered: Installing Ubuntu Server 18.04 with LAMP stack

sudo apt update
sudo apt install php7.2-{bcmath,cli,xml,mbstring,tokenizer,curl,zip,ldap,gd} git curl
sudo mysql -u root -p

<create the db, etc. per Snipe-IT documentation>

sudo mkdir /var/www/snipeit
sudo git clone https://github.com/snipe/snipe-it /var/www/snipeit/
cd /var/www/snipeit/
sudo cp .env.example .env
sudo vi .env
sudo curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | sudo php
sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/snipeit/
sudo php composer.phar install --no-dev --prefer-source
sudo php artisan key:generate
sudo vi /etc/apache2/sites-available/snipeit.conf
sudo a2ensite snipeit.conf
sudo a2dissite 000-default
sudo systemctl reload apache2

On to file contents...
snipeit.conf (/etc/apache2/sites-available/snipeit.conf)

<VirtualHost *:80>
DocumentRoot /var/www/snipeit/public

<Directory /var/www/snipeit/public>
Allow From All
AllowOverride None
Options None
</Directory>

RewriteEngine On
RewriteCond %{DOCUMENT_ROOT}%{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d
RewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} (.+)/$
RewriteRule ^ %1 [L,R=301]
RewriteCond %{DOCUMENT_ROOT}%{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d
RewriteCond %{DOCUMENT_ROOT}%{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
RewriteRule ^ /index.php [L]

ErrorLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/snipeit-error.log
CustomLog ${APACHE_LOG_DIR}/snipeit-access.log combined

</VirtualHost>

.env file changes:

--------------------------------------------
REQUIRED: BASIC APP SETTINGS
--------------------------------------------
APP_ENV=production
APP_DEBUG=false
APP_KEY=<string>
APP_URL=http://<ip>
APP_TIMEZONE='America/New_York'
APP_LOCALE=en
MAX_RESULTS=500

--------------------------------------------
REQUIRED: DATABASE SETTINGS
--------------------------------------------
DB_CONNECTION=mysql
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_DATABASE=snipeitdb
DB_USERNAME=snipeadmin
DB_PASSWORD=<pw>

That's a completely vanilla Ubuntu 18.04 install updated to latest with LAMP.
